commit 2d85fa632ce3918f7a52bf6555adec6e99464632
Author: cevr <seeve.c@gmail.com>
Date:   Wed Jun 17 14:30:04 2026 -0400

    feat(cms)(per-page-content): per-page /admin sections via DraftEditor + ListEdit
    
    Add a per-Page `/admin` editor (registration-launch Branch 5.5, ADR 0008,
    settled #5). One dynamic route (`admin/pages/:page`) edits any evergreen Page
    object through `DraftEditor` scoped to that page's `pageScope`, reusing the
    Branch-2 `ListEdit` add/remove/reorder machinery and the Branch-1 draft/publish
    pipeline — no new write path.
    
    - Draft page variants (`DraftFaqPage`/`DraftGivePage`/`DraftAboutPage`/
      `DraftArchivePage`): a freshly-added id-only list item is draft-valid yet
      publish-invalid until filled (ADR 0006). Pages without lists keep
      draftSchema === schema.
    - Registry `ObjectSpec` gains `draftSchema`; `DraftEditor`'s `objectCodec`
      decodes the draft through it and gates publish through the strict schema —
      the same split the site scope already has, so the reconciliation never forks.
    - Shared admin field/list controls hoisted to `routes/admin/controls.tsx`;
      the site editor (content.tsx) migrates to them (subtract-before-you-add).
    - Dashboard lists each per-page editor, driven by the closed PAGE_IDS registry.
    - RichText fields are shown read-only (the closed token model has no id-keyed
      nodes, so the identity-keyed merge cannot target a node in place).
    
    Tests: draft variants tolerate id-only adds but the strict schema blocks publish;
    per-page add→fill→publish goes live via getPage with no redeploy; publishing a
    page busts only that page's cache, not About's (ADR 0008 per-object isolation).

